<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROTHENBERG CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While I sympathize with David Rothenberg, I am concerned that the conditions of 
his father's parole represent an injustice to all of the victims of violent 
crimes. What warrants such exceptional safeguards while numerous less 
newsworthy victims share his same fears? Above all, his father is a threat to 
only one person while there are many paroled rapists and robbers who are 
threats to all of society. 
</P>
<P>
STEVE HOWARD 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
