</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seagate Technology Inc.: Second-quarter profit more than quadrupled to $35.8 
million on sales of $690.1 million, more than double the same period of 1988, 
the Scotts Valley, Calif., maker of computer hard disk drives said. The 1989 
results included the operations of Imprimis Technology, which Seagate acquired 
Oct. 2, 1989. Goodwill and other intangibles of about $114 million were 
recorded from the acquisition. 
</P>
