MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No Longer a Hogan, but Happy: Is revenge sweet? Ask Valerie Harper whose new 
CBS series "City" beat her old NBC show "The Hogan Family" on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
Harper won a lawsuit against the "Hogan" producers after they fired her. But 
will Harper's ratings victory continue through the season? The "City" debut 
scored a 13.9 rating and drew a 21% share of the audience, barely edging out 
the Hogan clan, which scored a 13.8 rating and 20 share. Each rating point 
equals 921,000 households. BETH KLEID 
</P>
