<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC &amp; DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Schaufuss Ousted From English Ballet: Noted Danish dancer Peter Schaufuss, 40, 
has been fired as artistic director of the English National Ballet, a post he 
has held since 1984. A National Ballet spokesman reached in London by telephone 
confirmed rumors that there had been problems between Schaufuss and the 
company's general administrator, Richard Jarman. 
</P>
<P>
"For sometime there has been a split there," said spokesman David Palmer. "But 
we've had two recent changes in the chairman of the board, and Pamela Lady 
Harlech has come in to straighten things out. Richard Jarman is still here, but 
his situation has got to be reviewed by the board too." Schaufuss was to dance 
in Southern California with members of the National Ballet at a March 11 AIDS 
benefit at the Pasadena Civic Auditorium. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Schaufuss 
</P>
