<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC &amp; DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Solti Plans Soviet, East Europe Tour: Sir Georg Solti said Wednesday he wants 
to take the Chicago Symphony Orchestra to the Soviet Union and his native 
Hungary in his last year as music director, the orchestra's 100th season. 
</P>
<P>
"We have an almost messianic message for Russia -- we want you to be part of 
Europe. I feverishly believe we've got to do it," the 78-year-old conductor 
said. An appearance in his native Budapest, if it too can be arranged, would be 
a "wonderful end," he said. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
