MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Grammy Show Shaping Up: Don Henley, Fine Young Cannibals, Bonnie Raitt, Billy 
Joel and Miles Davis are among the Grammy nominees who will perform live on the 
Feb. 21 awards telecast, which will also feature special tribute segments to 
lifetime achievement honorees Davis and Paul McCartney. Meryl Streep will 
present McCartney with his award, while Sting, Larry Carlton, Herbie Hancock 
and Branford Marsalis will perform in the tribute to Davis. The 
Grammy-sponsoring National Academy of Recording Arts &amp; Sciences also 
announced that Paula Abdul and Milli Vanilli are among those slated to serve as 
presenters on the show, which will take place at the Shrine Auditorium. BETH 
KLEID 
