Yugoslavia's Kosovo province. The government said the situation in the southern 
province is "deteriorating" after eight days of clashes between police and 
Albanians demanding political reforms. Masked Albanian nationalists, arms 
outstretched, participated in regional protests, right. At least 15 people have 
died since the ethnic Albanians, who are the majority in Serbian-ruled Kosovo, 
took to the streets. Agence France-Presse 
</P>
