<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CHULA VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A jury found a jail inmate guilty Wednesday of second-degree murder in the 
beating death of another prisoner in the South Bay jail in Chula Vista. 
</P>
<P>
After deliberating one day, the San Diego Superior Court jury convicted Steve 
Edward Morrison, 39, of San Diego, in the May 7, 1989, death of Luis Jose Mena, 
45. 
</P>
<P>
Mena was attacked on April 14, 1989, and suffered brain damage and a skull 
fracture, according to Deputy Dist. Atty. Evan Miller. Mena died three and a 
half weeks later in a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Miller said the motive for the attack was Morrison's hatred of child molesters. 
Mena had been convicted of molestation in 1985 and was back in jail on a parole 
violation when he was killed. 
</P>
<P>
Morrison was in jail at the time on a burglary charge and suspicion of 
violating parole, as he too has other felony convictions. 
</P>
<P>
Miller said Morrison faces a maximum sentence of 20 years to life in state 
prison, if he gets extra time for having prior felony offenses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
