<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN STABBED TO DEATH IN SUN VALLEY HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Sun Valley man was found stabbed to death in his bed Wednesday, apparently 
after a break-in, Los Angeles police reported. No arrests were made. 
</P>
<P>
Gregory Ellis Kellel-Sophiea, 38, was found dead in his home in the 9700 block 
of Orcas Avenue, Detective Al Ferrand said. 
</P>
<P>
Kellel-Sophiea was found about 3:15 a.m. by his wife, who had been sleeping in 
another room, Ferrand said. The wife and a 6-year-old daughter, whose 
identities were not released, apparently had not heard the attack, he said. 
</P>
<P>
"There is evidence that someone forced their way into the home, but we don't 
know why," Ferrand said. There was no indication that anything had been taken, 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were unable to determine if Kellel-Sophiea was attacked in his sleep or 
had fought his assailant. 
</P>
