<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TORREY PINES DROPS RBV BACK INTO PACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Torrey Pines held a one-point advantage going into the final quarter, then 
proceeded to outscore Rancho Buena Vista, 21-16, for a crucial, 64-58 Palomar 
League victory. 
</P>
<P>
RBV (9-9, 5-4), which had been hanging surprisingly close in the standings, 
fell three games behind league-leading Mt. Carmel and two behind Torrey Pines 
(20-2, 8-1). 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines' Kyle Armstrong led all scorers with 18. Carter Brown helped put 
RBV away late in the game with some crucial one-and-ones. He was five of seven 
from the line and finished with 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
RBV's Bond Schoefel entered the game in the second quarter and scored 10 of his 
16 points before halftime. Brad Grubaugh also scored 16 for the Longhorns. 
</P>
<P>
Daryl Parker, who entered the game with a 23.7-point average, was held to just 
12. 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 59, Fallbrook 54 -- Mt. Carmel (16-3, 9-0) maintained an eight-point 
lead through much of the game, but things tightened up with two minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
Fallbrook's Darnell Lee made a field goal, and Mt. Carmel's Shane Knight was 
called for a technical foul. Chris Miller made both free throws, then got the 
ball back on the inbounds and hit a three-pointer to cut Fallbrook's deficit to 
55-54. 
</P>
<P>
But Mt. Carmel's Ryan Wootton made a quick layup, Fallbrook (14-7, 5-4) missed 
its next shot, and the Sundevils then scored again to put it away. 
</P>
<P>
Poway 98, Orange Glen 46 -- Poway (13-5, 4-5) had four in double figures: Greg 
Sorrell (19), Frank Garrett (15), Kirk Hipple (14) and Zeke Awbrey (13). 
</P>
<P>
Avocado League 
</P>
<P>
El Camino 90, Ramona 51 -- Ramona (12-5, 4-4) never recovered from a two-point 
first quarter. Jeff Reeves led El Camino (14-5, 7-0) with 21 points. 
</P>
<P>
Oceanside 49, Escondido 30 -- Oceanside (10-10, 4-4) got off to a bad start, 
scoring only eight points in the first quarter, but Escondido (5-10, 3-5) had 
the bad finish: just 14 points in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
San Pasqual 87, San Marcos 48 -- Erik Meek led San Pasqual (13-5, 6-1) with 33 
points in only three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Girls 
</P>
<P>
Nonleague 
</P>
<P>
USDHS 65, Mira Mesa 48 -- Casey Burke led USDHS (12-2, 4-0) with 21 points and 
14 assists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020190-0087 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 169953 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 1, 1990, Thursday, San Diego County Edition 
