<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATLANTA MAYOR'S SON FINED ON DRUG CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maynard Jackson III, the son of Atlanta's mayor, was fined the maximum $150 
after he pleaded no contest to a misdemeanor charge of marijuana possession. 
</P>
<P>
The action came Tuesday in Atlanta Traffic Court, where Jackson also was found 
guilty of a charge of following too closely. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson was charged after a Jan. 9 traffic accident in Atlanta's Buckhead 
neighborhood, a day before his 19th birthday. Police said they found several 
marijuana cigarettes in his car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020190-0134 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 170072 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 1, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
