<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANCHEZ VICARIO ADVANCES EASILY IN TOKYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Second-seeded Arantxa Sanchez Vicario of Spain trounced Jo-Anne Faull of 
Australia, 6-1, 6-0, Wednesday and advanced to the quarterfinals of the Pan 
Pacific Open tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Also advancing was Switzerland's Manuela Maleeva, who routed American Terry 
Phelps, 6-2, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Steffi Graf plays her first match today against Nicole Jagerman of 
the Netherlands in the second round, and No. 4-seeded Mary Joe Fernandez faces 
Japan's Nana Miyagi. 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario, ranked fifth in the world, and Faull, ranked 69th, traded 
service breaks in the first two games, but the Australian was unable to win 
another game. 
</P>
<P>
"I shot passing shots and backhands very well," Sanchez Vicario said. "I am in 
top shape (because) I skipped the Australian Open and trained hard. 
</P>
<P>
The third-seeded Maleeva, firing six aces, overwhelmed an erratic Phelps, who 
is ranked 55th in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
