<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tony Dorsett told a Denver newspaper that he is retiring after 13 seasons as an 
NFL running back, but he has not informed the Denver Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
Said Jim Saccomano, Bronco spokesman: "Not unlike if one person says to 
another: 'Gee I'm going to quit my job.' That's all well and good but you need 
to tell the employer." 
</P>
<P>
Dorsett is the league's No. 2 all-time rusher with 12,739 yards. He sat out 
last season after undergoing knee surgery as a result of a training camp 
injury. It was his second season in Denver after 11 years with the Dallas 
Cowboys. 
</P>
