</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: CHARLOTTE HORNETS FIRE HARTER AS COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Charlotte Hornets fired Coach Dick Harter Wednesday and named assistant 
Gene Littles as interim coach, team officials said. 
</P>
<P>
"A skill that a coach must have is communication and it came to the point where 
I couldn't, as the owner, communicate with Dick and I know that he had lost his 
communication link with the players," owner George Shinn said. 
</P>
<P>
Harter, 58, was 8-32 this season and 28-92 in 1 1/2 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
"We know that the building process is a long one, and that was not a factor," 
said Carl Scheer, team president. "But the development of our younger players 
and the team is our priority, and with that in jeopardy, a change was 
necessary." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
