WASHINGTON, D.C.; 
</P>
<P>
SOVIETS SAY COPTERS WENT TO NICARAGUA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet Embassy confirmed that it finished shipping four MI-17 helicopters 
to Nicaragua last week, but it said the aircraft were built for civilian use. 
The statement, issued in Washington after news reports about the shipment, did 
not rule out the possibility that the helicopters may be diverted for military 
use. However, Secretary of State James A. Baker III earlier said the Soviets 
have given assurances that the helicopters will not be outfitted for military 
purposes. 
</P>
