<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN CHARGED UNDER NEW CHILD PORNOGRAPHY LAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 39-year-old Van Nuys man was charged Wednesday with possessing photographs, 
magazines and videotapes depicting children engaged in sex acts, the first use 
in Los Angeles of a new state law against possession of child pornography, the 
Los Angeles city attorney's office announced. 
</P>
<P>
Charged with one count under the new law was Larry Earl Wiese, 39, manager of 
the La Crescenta McDonald's restaurant. If convicted under the law that went 
into effect Jan. 1, Wiese faces up to one year in jail or a $2,500 fine or 
both. 
</P>
</TEXT>
