<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
ARTS FUNDING RULES GIVEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After two public hearings, a workshop and a pilot program last year, the 
year-old Pasadena Arts Commission has created new funding guidelines for the 
$180,000 Grants-in-Aid Program for 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Four funding eligibility categories and guidelines were approved Tuesday by the 
Board of Directors. They are: Category 1 -- Pasadena-based, nonprofit 
organizations with annual budgets of more than $500,000 are eligible for 
maximum grants of $45,000; Category 2 -- Pasadena-based nonprofit groups more 
than 3 years old can receive maximum grants of $7,500 with a matching 
fund-raising requirement of one-to-one; Category 3 -- Pasadena-based nonprofit 
groups less than 3 years old are eligible for grants of up to $5,000 with a 
matching fund-raising requirement of two-to-one; and Category 4 -- individual 
artists who live and work in Pasadena can receive $5,000 fellowships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
