<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BREA-OLINDA AVENGES LOSS TO VALENCIA WITH 6-2 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Ochs scored two goals and assisted on three others to lead Brea-Olinda 
High School to a 6-2 victory over Valencia in an Orange League soccer match 
Wednesday at Brea. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia (5-2 in league) had defeated Brea (10-7-2, 5-1-1), 4-1, in the first 
league meeting between the teams. 
</P>
<P>
"I was a bit surprised to be up 4-0 in the first half, but our players were 
hungry," Brea Coach Manny Toledo said. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Ferrier and Jeff Ortiz each scored two goals and goalkeeper Jeff 
Bettencourt had eight saves for the Wildcats. 
</P>
<P>
Peter Yanan and Joe Flammini each scored for Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 4, Santa Ana Valley 0 -- Gus Plasencia scored three goals to lead 
visiting Santa Ana. Jose Luis Ramirez also scored and Armando Guillen had five 
saves for Santa Ana (13-2-6, 5-0-2). 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 2, El Modena 0 -- Lance Anderson had eight saves in his 10th shutout 
of the season as Foothill (16-2-5, 3-0-4) won its first match after four 
consecutive ties. John Jacobs and Jeff Fischbeck scored in the first half for 
the Knights. David Lough had 12 saves for El Modena. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 2, Villa Park 0 -- Randy Campbell scored a goal in each half for 
visiting Canyon (9-7-4, 2-2-3). Goalkeeper Chris Snitko had six saves in his 
sixth shutout of the season. 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Katella 4, Loara 1 -- Armando Orizaba scored three goals in the second half to 
break a 1-1 tie at Katella. Jose Figuera also scored for Katella (11-6-4, 
2-3-2). Ryan Heise scored on a penalty kick in first half for Loara (1-19, 0-7) 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 5, Costa Mesa 0 -- Juan Strutton scored two goals for host Laguna 
Hills (17-4, 10-2). Eric Davis, Scott Clark and Jeff Cook also scored for 
Laguna Hills. Kirk Brown had six saves in his fifth shutout of the season. 
Costa Mesa is 1-15, 0-12. 
</P>
<P>
Orange 2, Woodbridge 0 -- Ricky Heimer and Justin Zayas scored for visiting 
Orange (14-0-3, 11-0-1), the No. 1-ranked team in Orange County. Woodbridge is 
7-8-2, 4-7-1. It was Orange's 11th shutout and goalie Tres Martin's eighth 
shutout. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills 1, Laguna Beach 0 -- Steve Kalajian scored with 15 minutes 
remaining for visiting Trabuco Hills (8-7-2, 6-4-2). 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
University 1, Estancia 1 -- Jose Medrano put host Estancia ahead, 1-0, five 
minutes before the half, and David Jacobson tied it with about 15 minutes left 
for University (8-6-3, 2-3-2). Estancia is 7-8-2, 4-2-1. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 1, Corona del Mar 0 -- Hernan De Santos scored in the first half for 
Saddleback (11-4-2, 4-2-1) at Corona del Mar. Goalkeeper Adrian Sevilla had 
seven saves in his sixth shutout. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 1, Tustin 1 -- David Pattison scored six minutes into the first 
half for host Newport Harbor (16-3-4, 4-0-3). Andy Bermudez scored midway 
through the second half for Tustin, which fell to 0-5-2 in league play. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 3, Westminster 0 -- Andrew Wind had two goals and Greg Biggins had 
one for host Ocean View (12-4-4, 4-1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Marina 1, Huntington Beach 0 -- At Huntington Beach, Ricky Rodriguez scored the 
only goal of the game one minute before halftime. Marina is 15-6-0, 6-1; 
Huntington Beach is 8-10-3, 0-4-3. 
</P>
