<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST CONFERENCE COACHES' POLLS; 
</P>
<P>
LONG BEACH TEAM TO BEAT IN BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach, which went to the College World Series last year in Dave 
Snow's first season as coach, has been chosen to win the Big West Conference 
baseball title in a poll of coaches. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton, coming off its worst record in 15 years, was picked to 
finish fifth. 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine was chosen seventh. 
</P>
