ROSEVILLE TICKET WINS JACKPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One ticket had all six winning numbers in Wednesday night's "Lotto 6-49" game, 
earning its holder a $4.7-million jackpot, California Lottery officials said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
The winning ticket was purchased in Roseville, about 15 miles northeast of 
Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
Four tickets had all five numbers plus the bonus number, each worth $328,000 
individual shares of a $1.3-million prize pool. Those tickets were purchased in 
La Puente, Chino, Riverside and Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
The jackpot for next Saturday's drawing is expected to reach $5 million. 
