<P>
CZECH STATUE OF STALIN ON BLOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buyers from West Germany and the United States have offered a Czechoslovak town 
more than its asking price for a statue of Josef Stalin. 
</P>
<P>
The CTK news agency said today that four buyers have bid for the 12-foot 
statue, advertised last week in a West German newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
CTK said buyers are prepared to pay more than the $50,000 asking price. 
</P>
<P>
The statue was put in storage during the 1968 Prague Spring reforms but 
reappeared after the Soviet-led invasion. It was removed again in December. 
</P>
