<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHRYSLER TO CLOSE ITS ST. LOUIS AUTO PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chrysler Corp. said today it will shut down its St. Louis car plant in 
September and transfer Dodge Daytona and Chrysler LeBaron production to 
factories in Delaware and Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
The closing will come seven months after the nation's No. 3 auto maker cuts 
production of the St. Louis No. 1 plant in half Feb. 12. In all, 3,700 
employees will be laid off in the two production cuts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
